<HEADLINE>Abuser detained</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>9</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974864385</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A MAN who posed as a priest as he preyed on young girls was ordered yesterday
to be detained in a mental hospital.
Gary Duff, of Deans South, Livingston, often wore a home-made ``dog collar'' as
he prowled children's playgrounds and the streets.
Defence solicitor Jim Kelly told Linlithgow Sheriff Court: ``He believed the
girls forced him to do it.''
Duff, 22, who is deaf, has spent the last five months in various hospitals and
prisons.
He admitted three charges of lewd and libidinous behaviour last year.
His victims were young girls aged six, seven, and nine. He picked them up to
kiss and molest them.
</TEXT>
