<HEADLINE>Hidden agenda</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>14</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Correspondence</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>974864388</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
HOW right you are to point out the daftness of the Department of Health's
latest pronouncement on safe drinking levels (December 13).
Is it being too cynical to suspect that this move is part of a hidden agenda to
counter the increasing numbers of elderly people who may need care over the
years?
R A Keith,
Easter Beltie House,
Glassel, Banchory.
</TEXT>
