<HEADLINE>Cup-tie called off again</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>31</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974864391</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE ill-fated Scottish Basketball Cup second-round tie between City of Aberdeen
Leopards and Glasgow Brightsiders, due to be played in Aberdeen today, is off
again, this time because no suitable referee is available.
Part of the problem is the Boroughmuir Invitation Tournament in Edinburgh,
which has attracted many of the top officials. Ironically, Brightsiders
withdrew from that event in order to fulfil their cup commitment.
The cup-tie should have been played last month. Then it was scheduled for
December 2, but a dispute over tip-off times led to its being rearranged for
today. Now it looks like being delayed until after the new year.
</TEXT>
