<HEADLINE>Boar-hunting</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>14</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Correspondence</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>974864392</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
I READ with dismay about       the proposed boar-hunting in Scotland.
We Scots are a noble race, albeit refined by centuries of oppression borne with
courageous fortitude. We are usually an example to less fortunate nations.
It is unthinkable that our hallowed soil should be contaminated by hideous
barbarism of this kind.
Let the potential hunter be corralled with a wild boar, without a gun, if he
wishes to show how brave he is.
Margaret E Souter,
7 Iain Road,
Bearsden.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
