<HEADLINE>Boy of 13 on murder charge</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>9</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974864402</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A 13-year-old boy appeared in court in Southampton yesterday accused of
murdering a tramp. He was released on conditional bail.
Alan Whittle, 50, died of burns 20 days after his clothing was allegedly set
alight in a park on September 17.
</TEXT>
