<HEADLINE>Citizen's trio share portrait</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>9</PAGE>
<FLAG>NEWS DIGEST</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>974864403</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Citizens' trio
share portrait
A PORTRAIT of the Citizens' Theatre's directorial triumvirate by Glasgow artist
Adrian Wiszniewski was unveiled yesterday at the theatre by Jeremy Isaacs.
The painting - of Giles Havergal, Robert David MacDonald, and Philip Prowse -
was commissioned by the Scottish National Portrait Gallery. It will be on
display at the People's Palace in Glasgow for two months before moving to the
Edinburgh gallery.
Chainsaw death
A TREE surgeon bled to death yesterday when a tree trunk he was cutting split,
throwing him to the ground along with his running chainsaw. The unnamed victim,
aged 47, was given mouth-to-mouth resuscitation but died within minutes at
Pitts Cleave quarry near Tavistock, Devon.
Tenement listed
A TENEMENT block in Dumbarton has been classed as a historic building. The
65-year-old Overtoun Terrace on Dumbarton's Glasgow Road has received category
C status, which means it is considered to be of local importance. The listing
affords the building protection from demolition, extension, or alteration.
Escapees held
FOUR men appeared in Dumbarton Sheriff Court yesterday accused of escaping from
custody at the same place 24 hours earlier. Eric Gray, 25, John Harrigan, 23,
Kenneth Proctor, 20, and Iain Brown, 20, all of Alexandria, were alleged to
have broken away as they were led to police vans. The four, who were all
recaptured within a few hours, made no plea and were remanded in custody.
Postal pay offer
MORE than 155,000 Royal Mail delivery and sorting staff are being urged by
their unions to accept an inflation-busting pay offer, revealed yesterday,
worth 3.5%.
Radiator recall
THOUSANDS of oil-filled electric radiators are being withdrawn because they
could catch fire or leak dangerous fumes. The Dimplex radiators in question
were sold mainly through B&amp;Q and Norweb stores and were marked with model
numbers: CR1507, CR2009, CR2009T, and BQ15CR.
</TEXT>
