<HEADLINE>Cost reductions</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>14</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Correspondence</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>974864406</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
I HAVE waited with interest to see if the concerns voiced by certain
politicians about the 7!s% cut in the Scottish Enterprise budget would be
matched by a storm of protest from the business community.
I have not been surprised at the lack of reaction.
I am quite sure that a host of businessmen would welcome being given the
challenge of achieving such a reduction. I am equally sure that such a
reduction could be achieved without in any way jeopardising the objectives of
either SE or the LECs.
Could The Herald not invite suggestions for cost reductions to be undertaken by
(or imposed upon) Scottish Enterprise?
I am sure a grateful Mr Forsyth would be pleased to provide some bottles of
House of Commons whisky for the most imaginative suggestions.
Donald Clark,
15 Middlepenny Road,
Langbank.
</TEXT>
