<DATE>951216</DATE>
<HEADLINE>NEWS DIGEST</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>7</PAGE>
<FLAG>News Digest</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>974864408</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Court stop-over
STORNOWAY Airport convened as a court yesterday to remand a man from the Uists
accused of house-breaking, because there was no fiscal or sheriff clerk
available at Lochmaddy. Lewis's sheriff redirected him by plane to Porterfield
Prison, Inverness.
Memorial
FRIENDS remembered the late Labour leader John Smith yesterday, as his widow,
Baroness Smith of Gilmorehill, presented a cheque in Edinburgh for #1000 to the
British Heart Foundation. It was raised by a memorial walk at Loch Katrine
earlier this year.
Meningitis victim
A FIVE-month-old boy has become the latest victim of meningitis. The child,
from Weymouth, Dorset, died hours after being admitted to hospital. The number
of cases of meningitis in Dorset has increased by more than 50% in the past
year.
Lost message
THE Government's Just Say No campaign against drugs has failed, say anti-drugs
campaigners. The Fast Forward Agency says negative images of the consequences
of drug use have served to alienate youngsters. It believes better financial
support for the volunteer agencies would be more effective.
</TEXT>
