<HEADLINE>Ban the Lords</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>14</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Correspondence</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>974864432</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE Wild Mammals (Protection) Bill has been killed off by the House of Lords.
It is abundantly clear that the House of Lords is an undemocratic institution
and is detrimental to the public interest. It ought to be abolished.
Mary Wilson,
27 Carswell Gardens,
Glasgow.
</TEXT>
