<RECORDNO>974864439</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Under the Moon, Martin Hayes (Green Linnet)
q The fiddling son of a fiddling father (who joins in on one set of jigs),
Martin Hayes has quickly earned a reputation for putting the tune before the
technique, a delicate approach that makes his carefully rationed slides and
slurs all the more potent.
Recorded in his native County Clare with apposite, well-scrubbed guitar and/or
accordion accompaniments, this is Irish fiddling at its most poetic, with a
bow-bouncing Foxhunter's Reel reminding us that Hayes in hooligan mode also can
be pretty awesome.
</TEXT>
