<TEXT>
q.THE phrase, poacher turned gamekeeper, could sum-up the happenings at East
End Park this afternoon, with poacher Andy Smith, keeper Andy Rhodes, and the
game league leaders Dunfermline against Airdrie. Smith, known as supersub in
his days with Airdrie, will be on the bench for the Fifers today with the
chance of playing for the first time since August, when he broke a small bone
in his right leg during a friendly.
Rhodes, whose former clubs include Dunfermline, has been bought by Airdrie to
cover the long-serving John Martin, who finally has had to give second best to
a leg injury which has been niggling him for months.
Dunfermline will keep the side who took four goals off Dundee last week, but
Airdrie will miss the suspended Steve Cooper and Sean Sweeney.
Dundee play host to St Johnstone with manager Jim Duffy back in the squad after
injury. Dundee also add Craig Tully and Darren Magee to a pool who will be
missing Paul Tosh, Jim Hamilton, and Gary McKeown because of suspension, and
Roddy Manley and Neil McCann through injury, while Saints, with Kevin McGowne
suspended, have Danny Griffin and Stuart McCluskey in their pool.
Dundee United travel to face Greenock Morton without Ray McKinnon and Maurice
Malpas because of injuries and midfielder David Hannah also is doubtful.
St Mirren have been hit by a flu virus, which will mean a late decision for
their line-up to face Clydebank at Love Street. Bottom clubs Hamilton and
Dumbarton square up at Firhill, with both in need of the points to pull
themselves closer to the main pack.
</TEXT>
