<TEXT>
Navy foils drug
smugglers
A ROYAL Navy frigate, HMS Brave, spotted a vessel jettisoning packages off
Jamaica this week. One bale, containing cocaine and marijuana, was picked up.
The crew surrendered and the US Coastguard said yesterday the haul was worth
#20m.
Church concern
LEADERS of Scotland's Christian churches yesterday appealed to the President of
Nigeria, General Sani Abacha, to release political prisoners and restore
independence of the courts. They expressed shock over the breakdown in human
rights.
Smith memorial
FRIENDS remembered the late Labour leader John Smith yesterday, as his widow,
Baroness Smith of Gilmorehill, presented a cheque in Edinburgh for #1000 to the
British Heart Foundation. It was raised by a memorial walk at Loch Katrine
earlier this year.
Academic jailed
OXFORD University academic Dr Simon Heighes, 33, one of Britain's leading
experts on baroque music, was jailed for two years in Oxford yesterday for the
theft of rare antique books from college libraries in Oxford and London.
Murder hunt
A MURDER inquiry started yesterday after the naked body of Northampton
prostitute Daniella White, 28, was found by a railway line in the area.
Mother missing
POLICE in Edinburgh are concerned about the ``out of character'' disappearance
from home of a 32-year-old mother of six. Mrs Wendy Adams, of Peffermill Road,
was last seen on November 29.
Rape charge
STIRLING man Jamie Thomson, 21, of Hope Street, Raploch, was remanded in the
town yesterday charged with the rape of a 19-year-old woman on Sunday.
</TEXT>
