<TEXT>
Soprano in Red: Lesley Garrett (Silva Classics)
q BLATANTLY nostalgic collection from La Garrett, the soprano who would be a
diva. Collection of old-fashioned, sentimental melters from operetta and
musical. The disc features Ivor Novello's We'll Gather Lilacs and Waltz of My
Heart, Noel Coward's If Love Were All, and selections from Sigmund Romberg,
Offenbach and Lehar (including, of course, the perennial tear-jerker, Vilja
from The Merry Widow). Though there are huge question marks over Garrett's
operatic abilities, she does this stuff - for which there is a huge market -
extremely well. With the Royal Philharmonic Concert Orchestra.
</TEXT>
