<DATE>951216</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Water charges</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>14</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Correspondence</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>974864475</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
I WAS horrified to read about the chaos that looms when local authorities have
to collect the water charges.
Many thousands will not pay in protest. If the cash is not collected the local
authorities will have the equivalent amount deducted from their budgets and
therefore from the likes of education, social work, etc.
The water boards get their money, the vulnerable suffer, and the Government,
which set up the legislation, can sit back and laugh all the way to the bank.
Lionel G Hawes,
50 Kingsacre Road,
Glasgow.
</TEXT>
