<DOCNO>GH951216-000094</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH951216-000094</DOCID>
<DATE>951216</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Children's cartoon sex shock</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>5</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974864480</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
TWO children watching a new Pocahontas cartoon video saw a pornographic film
flash on the screen.
A supermarket chain yesterday took the movie, which has no connection with the
Disney blockbuster Pocahontas, off its shelves after the girls' shocked mother,
Mrs Debbie Lewis, handed the video to the police.
The #3 cartoon had been taped over a film showing lesbian sex scenes. Trading
standards officers have warned other parents to beware if they have bought The
Adventures of Pocahontas.
Sarah Lewis, 11, and her sister Jodie, nine, watched the movie at their
grandmother's home. Mrs Lewis, 36, of Port Talbot, West Glamorgan, said: ``The
cartoon lasted 26 minutes and suddenly ran straight into these sex scenes.''
The video was sold by supermarket chain Hyper Value, which has 21 stores across
Wales and the West Country. Trading standards officers are now trying to
contact the makers, World Class Entertainment of London.
</TEXT>
