<DATE>951216</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Smashing day for Rod Stewart</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974864538</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
ROCK star Rod Stewart's wedding anniversary celebrations were marred last night
as his family was showered in broken glass.
The singer and his wife Rachel Hunter reaffirmed their vows in a church service
at Marlow, Buckinghamshire, and were being taken to a hotel in a horse-drawn
carriage when a bodyguard accidentally put his arm through a window.
Shards narrowly missed the children, Liam, one, and three-year-old Renee. The
girl had to be lifted out in tears.
One onlooker said: ``There must have been at least seven photographers chasing
them across the bridge. In his haste to stop one of them getting a picture of
the couple as they turned into the hotel, one of the minders smashed a window
on the carriage.''
Among the 30 guests at All Saints Church, Marlow, were family and friends,
including actress Susan George.
Four bouncers had earlier jogged alongside the horses as they ferried the
wedding party across a bridge from the car park at the Compleat Angler Hotel.
As Stewart, 50, and his wife emerged from the church, a piper played Flower of
Scotland.
The glass accident happened as they returned to the hotel for a reception.
Church rector, the Rev Nicholas Maloney, carried out the service on the
couple's fifth wedding anniversary.
He said it had been a service of prayer and dedication, adding that ``they
wanted to renew their vows on their wedding anniversary with their family and
friends''.
</TEXT>
