<HEADLINE>Smith and Fraser set records in vain</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>ELSPETH BURNSIDE</BYLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>30</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974864543</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
GRAEME Smith and Fraser Walker both set Scottish records at the Uncle Ben's
Winter Challenge in Sheffield yesterday - but each failed to strike gold.
For Smith, the European Championship silver medallist and defending champion, a
Scottish record of 14min 49.71sec still left him an astonishing nine seconds
behind the winner, Leeds' Ian Wilson, whose 14-40.69 was almost seven seconds
inside the old British record.
Walker lowered his own Scottish record in the 50m back-stroke to 26.46sec but
had to settle for fifth. Neil Willey won in a British record 24.88.
q.BRYAN Morgan, the Dunfermline High schoolboy, collected the 50m back-stroke
title in a British junior record 28.46, at yesterday's Scottish Winter
Championships at Ayr.
Scholarship students Susan Colling and Pauline McLean completed a Stirling
University double. Colling won the 800m free-style in 9-06.08, while McLean
held off double Olympian Alison Sheppard to win the 50m back-stroke in 30.36.
Sheppard, five days after returning from six weeks' training in Canada, struck
gold in the 200m medley and 50m free-style. Winners:
Men: 50m butterfly - C Black (Arbroath St Thomas) 26.01. 50m back-stroke - B
Morgan (Carnegie) 27.32. 50m breast-stroke - J-P Shearer (Inverclyde) 30.70.
50m free-style - A Pullan (Leatherhead) 23.99. 200m medley - I Edmond
(Aberdeen) 2min 10.72sec. 1500m free-style - A Lane (Stirling) 16-14.28.
Women: 50m butterfly - G Anderson (Eastwood) 30.55. 50m back-stroke - P McLean
(Stirling) 30.36. 50m breast-stroke - B Robertson (Aberdeen) 34.95. 50m
free-style - A Sheppard (Milngavie &amp; Bearsden) 26.03. 200m medley - Sheppard
2-21.01. 800m free-style - S Colling (Stirling)                9-06.08.
