<TEXT>
Special travel
correspondent
Katie Wood selects the best bargains
n.For a Christmas dripping with Bing Crosby sentimentality you can't beat the
White Hart Inns Christmas Experience. This group of hotels - with 72 properties
throughout the UK - is offering two types of festive packages awash with
carol-singing youngsters, log fires and Dickensian costume. Prices start at #95
per person per night. If you have relatives coming from abroad looking for an
olde-worlde experience, this is the one to go for. In Scotland their properties
are in Peebles, Perth and Pitlochry.
n.Easyjet's service from Edinburgh to Luton has now commenced. Note that the
#29 single is available on a first-come basis. It's also worth noting that
Easyjet's offer is the only one that does not insist on a Saturday night stay
over. For reservations call 01582 445566.
n.FOLLOWING its #2.5 million renovations, the Adam mansion of Duff House, near
Banff, is now functioning as a country house gallery. Due to its successful
season since opening in April, the decision has been taken to keep the house
open throughout the year. You don't need a better excuse for a short break or
Sunday run to this glorious part of Scotland. Hours are 10am to 5pm
Thursdays-Sundays. If you want to make a short break of it and enjoy a stay in
Grampian Region using Autumn Gold discounts, call 01224 636363.
n.Looking for skiing insurance at a bargain price? Inter Assurance offer a week
in Europe for #21 and #46.50 for two weeks worldwide. A family can have cover
in Europe for #47 a week and #118 for a fortnight worldwide. This also covers
off-piste skiing, snowboarding, snowmobiles and tobogganing. Call 01252 717766.
n.How about a bargain Christmas in Germany in the Moselle Valley? Moswin Tours
have a departure on December 23 for a six-day holiday based in the town of
Bernkastel-Kues. The cost is #275 including return coach travel, five nights
half board hotel accommodation with seasonal meals and entertainments. Call
0116 271 9922.
n.Italy anyone? For unbeatable flight prices direct from Scotland contact the
Italian specialist Solemar in Glasgow. Flights for skiing and for city breaks
or summer holidays are all available. A sample price is departing February 12
to Venice at #159 return. Call 0141 333 0533.
n.Hawaii has a certain ring when the drizzle's coming down the back of your
neck and the Scottish winter takes grip. The cost of a break to the Hawaiian
Islands is less than perhaps you would think. Page &amp; Moy have a holiday from
Glasgow for #925 per person for three weeks - they are currently offering three
weeks for the price of two. Call 0116 252 4444.
n.Skibound is offering Glasgow departures from mid-February to mid-April, 1996.
Prices start at #254 per person for return flights direct to Lyon, transfers
and seven night half-board accommodation at Alpe d'Huez in a Skibound Club
hotel. These flights also serve the Italian Alps. Travel agents have brochures.
n.An offer on flight deals include Tenerife on December 30 for #234, Malaga on
December 28 for #204, and Las Palmas on December 23 for #199. All from Glasgow
Airport. Call 0141 303 0303.
n.Northern Cyprus is on offer between January 1 -March 17 for #289 a week per
person from London. Special company Metak have apartments eight miles from
Kyrenia. Call 0171 935 6961.
n.If a study holiday appeals, the School of Continuing Education in Kent is
organising more than 80 different courses in 14 locations throughout the UK
next summer. Using their Summer Academy programme themes, courses in the Arts,
Heritage, Countryside and Personal Development, are being held from June 29 to
August 31 in centres of learning such as the universities of Oxford, Cambridge,
Durham and Stirling. No prior knowledge of a subject is necessary and the
courses offer an opportunity for students to gain academic credit which could
lead to an award.
Prices start at #340 and include full board accommodation for six or seven
nights, tuition and course-related excursions. For a free brochure call 01227
470402, or write to the Marketing and Reservations Co-ordinator, Summer
Academy, Keynes College, Canterbury, Kent CT2 7NP.
n.Next May sees the start of Prestwick to Orlando flights from Sir Freddy
Laker. Prices start at an impressively low #399, and passengers can take
advantage of free ScotRail tickets to and from Prestwick to anywhere in
Scotland.
n.Post Office Counters has announced a major new deal to enable customers to
apply for 10-year passports through 1500 main post offices across the UK from
next month. This follows the withdrawal of British Visitor passports from
December 31.
